205051;instagram;2019-02-08 12:42:43;FALSE;we visited rosewood asylum. we just walked around
column3: we thought about the dark history it has. we saw the decay. the peeling paint
column5: rotting floorboards. i got to thinking this morning. recovery is like this photo. whatever you are going through
column6: once you commit to growing and changing for the better
column7: it can feel a lot like this. feelings and emotions peeling off the walls of your heart
column8: abandoned pieces of a former time taking up space in your life. your very foundation
column9: the core of what you knew to be true seemingly rotting away. will i ever be beautiful again? how will i stand? how can i move forward in all this ugly? truth is
column10: things will look worse before they look better. think of those house flipping shows where someone takes an old
column12: unlivable home and turns it beautiful again. same is true for us. for recovery. for change. we must peel back and scrape off that old paint
column13: the negative feelings and lies we painted on our hearts and in our minds. we must be willing to let go of the junk and baggage holding us back and weighing us down. we must rebuild a foundation on truth. it will be hard and it may look ugly... but slowly
column15: and over time you will once again see the beauty that was hidden. it will emerge again. it can be rebuilt and made new. even more beautiful than before ❤🦋

column1: 205059;instagram;2019-02-08 12:53:15;FALSE;"it was the year king uzziah died: (lol) no. it was year 2002-2003 maybe... i was well into entrepenuership. those shirts say "" glam squad"". i had just bought a bulk to sell from the money my lastest ""distributor"" had given me. in exchange for cars
column4: nights of ectasy...sex and undoubtely my soul. ✨ or so he thought✨ i was not just kneeling down
column5: dang near on my knees in this pic but on my way to being brought to my knees in life by the devil himself. no taller than my waist but a giant in the kingdom of darkness.

column1: what i didn't know was no giant can defeat me...because i had already been chosen. last friday i was sitting in a revival service and someone sent me this. (tears) she said look how far we've come. 🙌 i would have never saw me sitting in a church
column3: on a friday night @theacceleratordc (shameless plug) but i am greatful that i know god to be a strong deliverer. a savior. a keeper of his word.  idk know where you might me in your process of healing
column4: deliverance or damascus experience. you've been knocked down...yes. but it's only to show god's glory in getting back up. you set out to destroy others (or yourself) but god has already called you to be a deliverer. you are not big enough to stop his plan for your life. you don't see it now because you're blind; but what you don't know is you have to be to know how to lead others thru faith (what cannot be seen). to turn them from the power of satan. come outta agreement w. the devil. turn your back on people
column5: places and things that take you away from god. this next season is a season called sober.  get ready for an eye opening testimony that god is 🙌

column1: 205112;instagram;2019-02-08 13:58:06;FALSE;"true? i think we are all guilty of this in some facet of our lives. i know i am! 🙋🏻‍♀️ so the question becomes what are we gonna do about it?  how do we get past our own bullshit and do something? 🤷🏻‍♀️ i don’t purport to have all the answers
column2: that’s for damn sure.  but doing some soul-searching might give us a clue. ask yourself
column3: what are you most afraid of?  play out the best and the worst case scenarios. there is a 99% chance that neither of those scenarios will actually happen. what typically happens is somewhere in the middle. and just remember
column4: the middle is manageable. we can handle the middle
column5: right?  we have a 100% track record so far

column1: so let’s do it! let’s pull up our “big kid pants” and call ourselves out on our own bullshit... so we can grow and get better. let’s play out those scenarios. then let’s figure out what bite-sized actions are necessary to get us closer to where we wanna be and let’s see what happens. 💫
i will see ya out there - somewhere in the middle! 🥰 .

column1: hello everyone! i’m lexi from ohio and i’m 26 years old
column3: and an aspiring influencer. milani santina marie is my beautiful
column5: spunky 7 month old! she has made me a mommy and is my only as of now.

column1: motherhood hasn’t been easy! my life before motherhood was far from easy. i was forced to grow up fast! i had a motherly mentality since i can remember as it was my survival instincts kicking in to care for my siblings. i’m a survivor of childhood/incest rape. as bad as it sounds
column2: it taught me how i didn’t want to be as a mother and what i needed to do to be a real parent. .

column1: milani was born 5 weeks premature. my labor was traumatic and she has since been diagnosed with a swallowing disability call dysphasia. she has to see speech therapy and have liquids thickened. on top of that she was a colic infant
column3: and gerd! we’ve had a tough ride so far but that smile keeps me going.

column1: this community i have met from @mommy_instafriends
column2: has been one of the main forms of support at some points. when i felt i had no one to turn to
column3: this community of women were there. i’m here to support each of you! and i can’t wait to learn more about you 🖤

column1: 205119;instagram;2019-02-08 14:01:51;FALSE;"¿por qué los cuerpos desnudos de las mujeres generan tanto revuelo? nunca comprenderé la persecución a las mujeres que deciden compartir fotografías de sus cuerpos en las redes sociales.

column2: porque las redes censuren en el siglo xxi los desnudos y segundo
column3: porque sé que muchas reciben acoso cibernético como si por el hecho de mostrarse desnudas ya tuvieran derecho a decirles lo que quieran.

column2: las feministas no buscamos vuestro piropo hacia nuestro cuerpo. en esas imágenes hay arte
column5: sentimientos y reivindicación. para mí esas fotografías significan la libertad que muchas anhelamos y que nuestro alrededor intenta censurar. basta ya de poner límites a nuestras decisiones y de decidir sobre nuestros cuerpos.

column1: hace tiempo compartía que me impactan los machistas que se sienten molestos con los cuerpos desnudos de las mujeres. si ellos son los primeros que lo consumen
column2: es como si quisieran censurar todo aquello que no les pertenece.

column1: en mi última etapa en instagram he podido valorar lo bonito que es ver que cada vez más mujeres vamos descubriendo nuestro cuerpo sin miedo (o con él) a recibir todos esos mensajes machistas.

y quizá algunos machistas todavía  se pregunten qué son esos mensajes heteropatriarcales... todos aquellos que no respetan a la mujer que los reciben: tanto los piropos fuera de admirar su profesionalidad
column2: siguiendo por los que simplemente envían sus miembros en mensajes directos hasta los que llenan sus cuentas de insultos y mensajes de odio. ¿no creéis que es hora de que el desnudo de la mujer se normalice? ¿que dejen de censurarnos en las redes sociales? ¿que podamos elegir lo que compartimos? estamos en el momento de conseguir avances también en estos medios sociales pero para ello necesitamos analizar la raíz del problema.

obviamente todas las mujeres se merecen mi respeto pero incluso más las que son valientes y nos abren camino a las demás hacia la libertad. ¿por qué no lo tienen los machistas? ¿les da miedo nuestra libertad?

column1: 205151;instagram;2019-02-08 14:30:35;FALSE;"i was a young 26-year old director at the ymca of metropolitan milwaukee at one of their branches. i started finding myself unawaringly helping not only the young girls working for me but women members i had become friends with. i became a mentor
column6: and social worker. often times i put myself in extremely dangerous situations which i didn't think twice about until i told someone what i did and they brought it to my attention. one example
column7: i received a call from a young female staff member around 2:30 am to come get her because her boyfriend was beating her and pulled out a gun and was going to kill her. she trapped herself in a room and told me where to come and i helped her escape out of a window. she always hugged and kissed me when i saw her and said i saved her life. ***submit your story of courage here: http://illuminatefilmfestival.com/acts-of-courage-form

column1: 一位女戰地記者的真實經歷，電影拍出來不只是想世人歌頌她為了披露戰爭真相而犧牲的偉大事蹟，不是想你用兩小時佩服她的勇敢後明天繼續吃喝玩樂”life goes on”，它也不是想說這個世界有人過得比你更慘要你好好珍惜生命。
了解戰爭可恨之處後，我們對人生有沒有另一種看法？我們的能力有限，或許每人多做一點，這個世界會美好多一點，哪怕只有一點點。就像marie colvin，她選擇留守做那段直播讓全世界知道最真實的戰況，雖然沒有令敍利亞即時停火，還有五十萬平民於她死後遇難，但這部電影的出現是因為她，她以生命影響更多人的生命。
突然想起那些整天喊著父權社會的禍害，聲援#metoo 的女權主義者，除了站在道德高地批判男性外，不知道她們有沒有像marie colvin的勇氣走訪中東國家為當地女性的人權發聲呢？

column1: 205168;instagram;2019-02-08 14:52:42;FALSE;"女性向けコワーキングスペースが増加、米国　ヨガや保育など提供も
'my happy place.' workspaces for women rise in #metoo era
new post @newsphere_jp  設立から1年のワークスペース、「モダンウェル」。一歩足を踏み入れると、まるで快適なスパを訪れたような感覚になる。こざっぱりしたオフィスにはフェイクファーで覆われたスツールや、燃え盛る炎を囲む快適なアームチェアなど、居心地の良い空間が広がっている。あちこちに置かれたテーブルには、ノートパソコンを広げる女性たちの姿がある。
ここに、男性の姿はない。

entering the year-old workspace modernwell feels like coming into a comfortable spa. clean lines give way to cozy touches like footstools covered with faux fur and a roaring fire surrounded by comfortable armchairs. women type away on laptops at tables scattered throughout.
there is not a man in sight.

column1: it’s 2019. there is absolutely no reason why we should continue having animals sent to slaughter for food or fashion. there are so many different varieties of protein rich food and meat substitutes on the market and there are so many different types of natural and organic fabric we could be using to substitute for suede
column2: leather and fur. as a species we like to pride ourselves on being “evolved” but when it comes to our dietary choices we subscribe to the caveman mentality. an evolved species would not continue to harm animals and the planet for sheer enjoyment. an “evolved” species would find better alternatives to progress forward. we have alternatives to meat
column4: and animal skin but a lot of us are still very reluctant to change. the easiest thing to do is not care what happens to animals. this is very irresponsible because we are taking the innocent lives of these poor creatures for absolutely no reason at all in 2019. to my non-vegan followers please make the connection today! the downfall of our species will come at the hands of our own pride and ego. it is ok to show compassion for those that are vulnerable. it doesn’t make you soft! it makes you smart! go vegan for the animals! #respectlife #loveanimals #letthembe #theirlivesmatter #guesswhat #animallovers #animalkingdom #familyiseverything #savetheocean #savetheearth #peaceandlove #govegan #crueltyfree #environment #environmentalist #planetearth #metoo #wildlife #wildlife_perfection #animalshaverights #proteina #babyanimals #donttakeourplanetforgranted";;en;#respectlife

column1: completely subverting the highly traditional period drama genre
column2: yorgos lanthimos is able to upturn that tradition and completely revolutionise the genre in what is one of the most revolutionary films of the year. following the story of queen anne in early 18th century england
column3: we witness a highly witty and intelligently built game of struggle for power
column6: fight each other to win the favour of the queen. with the use of imaginative camera movements and ""fish eye"" camera lenses
column7: we enter the distorted world of british aristocracy in an incredible satire of power and the monarchy. everyone is absolutely outstanding in this film. olivia colman does a perfect performance as the gout-ridden and infantile queen of a huge european empire. and rachel weisz and emma stone are equally perfect as two women struggling for power in a world seemingly (and big emphasis on ""seemingly"") controlled by men. yorgos lanthimos crafts one of the most intelligent films of the year
column8: with absolute control over his material
column9: brilliantly being able to use the dignity of the aristocracy and the period drama genre against itself
column10: showing the rot and the reality behind the performative perfection of the aristocracy. in a time of #metoo
column11: this is also a brilliant feminist story that shows that who really runs the world isn't men. the men in the favourite are completely ridiculed and shown as mere slaves to gossip and their carnal desires as the women focus on what really matters - power - acting with their charm and behind the scenes. it shows the ugliness of power
column12: possessing a strong critique to it and those that are in such a position. the favourite is a feminist film both for showing women in power and for showing the ugliness inherent in it. this is one of the most technically and artistically impressive films of the year
column13: with incredible costume and production design
column14: and one of the most important films of the year. it's definitely something that needs to be experienced and one of lanthimos' (who has quickly become one of my favourite directors right now) best films.";;en;#metoo

column1: mas não é de hoje que se discute o machismo no meio artístico. em 1984
column4: promoveu a exposição an international survey of recent painting and sculpture
column5: que buscava reunir os artistas mais importantes da década. entre 165 pintores e escultores selecionados pela curadoria
column7: só 13 eram do sexo feminino. revoltadas pela falta de representação nas artes
column8: um grupo de mulheres resolveu fazer um protesto em frente ao museu. ao serem ignoradas
column9: passaram a espalhar cartazes pela cidade enquanto vestiam máscaras de gorila. surgiu ali o grupo guerrilla girls

column6: deixando outras oficinas somente para homens.

column2: sendo desencorajadas a seguirem caminhos considerados “masculinos”. a própria autora do presente texto é musicista há dez anos e sempre é obrigada a provar seu talento e incontáveis vezes é substituída por homens que nem sempre têm conhecimento suficiente.

em todo lugar ouvem-se músicas com letras machistas como a citada anteriormente e o assédio a artistas do sexo feminino dificilmente é denunciado por medo do agressor e receio de terem sua carreira prejudicada.

column1: my name is lillian rodriguez. i am a student at waubonsie valley high school
column2: one of the best high schools in the district.
i watched as my female family members ran from relationship to relationship with men. i was confused why they’d cry
column3: but i just assumed it was a bad breakup.

column1: i got a little older and eventually learned why. -
i got a boyfriend freshman year. he was an amazing
column4: with a cute smile. one day
column5: he asked me if he could kiss me. i said
column7: i don’t really feel comfortable with that.” i didn’t hear from him until he decided that i had been punished enough for defying him. he asked me what i’d do if he did a) b) or c). i said i was uncomfortable
column8: but not verbally. i didn’t want to be left like that again. -

column1: i said yes to everything we did
column2: because i didn’t want to be ignored by my significant other. everything escalated
column4: “no” wasn’t in my vocabulary. i told him i was raised to be afraid of most men. he yelled at me for thinking such a thing.

column1: i was hurt and confused. he got things out of me that i vowed to myself to never do. images
column4: gestures. one day he cornered me in the stairwell after i cried about being scared of him

column1: we broke up a couple months later. now
column3: i have accepted what happened to me. -

column1: he still goes to my school. he still looks at me in the hallways. he still smirks when i lock eyes with him and freeze.
this is what happened to me. this is a very real thing. this isn’t just something that you hear of in movies and viral social media
assault is real. and it happens at your school.
i am a very lucky case in which i refused to be alone with him even when we were dating
column3: there was a very positive chance i would’ve been raped. -

column1: американская модель #кэтринмайорга в 2009 году подала в полицию заявление об изнасиловании
column2: но при этом не раскрыла имя нападавшего (криштиану роналду). у нее были необходимые медицинские свидетельства. • в 2010-м она подписала документ с юристами роналду и получила 375 тысяч долларов за молчание. • в апреле 2017-го об истории впервые написал der spiegel на основе документов football leaks. к журналистам попала переписка роналду с юристом. • к осени 2018-го кэтрин майорга вдохновилась волной #metoo (под этим хэштегом жертвы сексуального насилия делятся своими историями – sports.ru) и рассказала обо всем подробно
column3: нарушив договор с юристами роналду. • в сентябре 2018-го полиция вегаса возобновила дело. • роналду все отрицает. говорит
column4: что женщина хочет прославиться за счет его имени. «она же не в карты к нему в номер пришла играть. девушка знала
column5: чем они будут заниматься. я своего сына знаю»

column1: 205348;instagram;2019-02-08 17:22:13;FALSE;"qotd: do you read nonfiction? what's the last nonfiction book you read?

what's wrong with being an angry feminist? not a dang thing!! it's okay to be angry and we should turn that anger into positive action that can help improve the world around us. happy feminist friday!
good and mad: the revolutionary power of women's anger | rebecca traister

column2: the new york times bestselling author of all the single ladies comes a vital
column3: incisive exploration into the transformative power of female anger and its ability to transcend into a political movement.

column2: it seems as if women’s anger has suddenly erupted into the public conversation. but long before pantsuit nation
column5: women’s anger was not only politically catalytic—but politically problematic. the story of female fury and its cultural significance demonstrates the long history of bitter resentment that has enshrouded women’s slow rise to political power in america
column6: as well as the ways that anger is received when it comes from women as opposed to when it comes from men.

column1: 205430;instagram;2019-02-08 18:18:43;FALSE;"_“eu ser legal com você não significa que estou te dando mole."" ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
alguma vez você já pensou em falar essa frase para alguém? ☺

column3: mas algumas vezes essas atitudes acabam sendo mal interpretadas.

column1: infelizmente vivemos em uma sociedade machista que parece não conseguir diferenciar o ""ser legal” do “tô te dando mole”. e quando essa saia justa acontece no local de trabalho
claro que não são todos os homens
column2: ainda bem! há aqueles que sabem manter uma boa conversa sem ter malícias escusas.

column1: por óbvio só fazer cara feia não vai resolver
column3: não dão uma resposta atravessada por medo das consequências.

column1: se for no ambiente profissional então
é realmente um desafio que muuuuitas mulheres vivem diariamente. veja a campanha #metoo das atrizes de hollywood. essa situação não escolhe lugar e nem classe social
column2: ela pode acontecer com qualquer uma de nós. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: está mais do que na hora de termos a coragem de falar
column2: expor e ter firmeza na hora de se expressar e dizer _não_.🚫🤚
uma conversa sincera e civilizada pode evitar muitos aborrecimentos. pode até parecer meio bobo
column3: mas sentar e falar sobre o assunto tende solucionar muitos problemas.

column1: ao final da conversa de duas uma. você pode ter sido mal interpretada ✔ou
column3: a pessoa agiu de forma errada mesmo.❌ empodere-se e esclareça os pontos. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: caso o homem do outro lado da conversa ""não queira"" entender a sua vontade
column2: não hesite em exercer seus direitos.🚔 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: ele vai perceber que ser legal não é sinônimo de ser boba (desculpa o termo 😉). vamos juntas ser #donadomundo
column2: donas do nosso mundo. isso pode ajudar você e outras mulheres! 💁🏻‍♀️🌍

column1: 205447;instagram;2019-02-08 18:45:05;FALSE;"this is sarai (our now 25 year old special needs daughter) with her uncle brian.  she has always been one that loves to laugh and play around.  she only does this now with family or people she’s known for at least 20+ years.  i look back thinking how carefree she was at this time.  i remember trying to tame her down a little
column2: because i didn’t want people to get annoyed at her.  the last few days i’ve been thinking about ptsd (she was diagnosed with this years ago) it’s so sad that people go through this and that it can last for so long.  does it get better with time? i think it would have
column3: but then she had other tragedies that kept her tied to ptsd.  i think it may be harder for her too
column5: because she is an obsessive person anyways about things
column6: and so she’s never able to let things go.  she still talks about things happening to her like they were yesterday and it’s been 20 years.

column1: watching this play in 2019 in the context of a long overdue reckoning with male violence is to see how misogyny is intertwined with racism and xenophobia

column1: iago’s manipulation and othello’s transformation from loving newlywed to murderer are shocking. if we are to believe iago
column2: there are two reasons for his cruelty: revenge for sexual infidelity and professional jealousy of sorts. but neither explanation has struck most playgoers as sufficient

column1: like many men who sexually abuse and harass women
column2: who rape and murder girlfriends and wives
column3: iago blends in with acceptable masculine norms of behavior toward girls and women. audiences have become conditioned to pose the question “why does he do it?” about iago
column4: and to focus on the tangle of emotions that tie him to othello. a fascination with violent men and a routine attribution of interest and significance to them makes this question central to an experience of the play.

column1: but we have overlooked an equally urgent question: why is desdemona relegated to plot device? how does the habitual focus on violent men erase the victims of their violence? why doesn’t the misogyny at the heart of iago’s plotting garner more attention by playgoers?
our conditioning to accept misogyny as normal is surely part of the answer. to believe women faithless and men predatory by nature is one of our gender myths. yet despite their fidelity

column1: 205503;instagram;2019-02-08 19:57:27;FALSE;"decided to stop by @bevmo_co and asked about how to get a non alcoholic beer into the store and was treated with such rudeness.

my question was if the entire company's brand is non alcoholic does it need to follow the same rules as an alcohol distributor or is it more along the lines of selling kombucha and the man in charge seemed to assume that i am a vendor trying to sell something and just told me to ask corporate
column2: they handle the alcohol distributor. however that wasn't my question as the entire brand's concept is non alcoholic craft beer and eventually he admitted he had no idea and never ever heard of the concept of non alcoholic beer companies.

column1: then i expressed that my questions are coming from a place of wanting to celebrate my soberity and he just looked at his phone and said there are bigger problems in addiction and i explained to him that even people who are struggling with drugs need non alcoholic beer so they don't relapse into harder drugs and alcohol is the gateway.
he said he has no knowledge of addiction and i am going to be stuck with water and soda for the rest of my life. i am so incredibly annoyed with the response to simply wanting to spend money lol
the way people are expected to be sober is literally impossible given the reality of the stigma
column2: even when you have done the impossible and found two years of sobriety
column3: paid off all your debt and have money to spend you get treated like shit! yay 🙌

column1: that’s what we called it in my house growing up. my mom used to make it for my dad to take on his hunting trips.
my husbands family makes something similar (although not nearly as tasty 😉) during the holidays.

whatever you want to call them the good news is you can make them whenever you want!! i made some last night for a friend who mentioned a while back that she liked them. it’s her birthday! 🎈🍰 give them a try and let me know what you think. i’m pretty sure you’re bound to be sneaking back to the kitchen for a second and third.
1. grease the bottom and sides of a 9x13 dish with butter.
2. combine all ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
3. cook until candy thermometer reads 245. make sure to stir continuously.
4. pour into 9x13 pan. let cool up to 2 hours. cut into bite sized pieces and wrap in wax paper.

column1:
;​​португалец отрицает все обвинения . полиция лас-вегаса начала расследование по делу нападающего ювентуса криштиану роналду , которого обвиняют в изнасиловании девушки , сообщает guardian . « департамент полиции лас-вегаса получил сообщение о нападении 13 июня 2009 года . во время составления отчета жертва не назвала детективам место происшествия и не предоставила описание подозреваемого . был проведен медицинский осмотр . по состоянию на сентябрь 2018 года дело было возобновлено , и наши детективы изучают информацию , которую предоставила жертва . никаких подробных сведений опубликовано не будет » , – говорится в сообщении департамента полиции лас-вегаса . причиной для возобновления дела стало интервью американки кэтрин майорги немецкой газете der spiegel , в котором она рассказала о ситуации . майорги отметила , что получила 375 тысяч долларов за молчание от криштиану роналду , но в связи с движением она решила сделать все подробности публичными . издание daily mail , в свою очередь , сообщает , что португалец уже нанял детектива следить за девушкой . таким образом , роналду хочет дискредитировать 34-летнею американку . адвокаты звездного нападающего , как и сам дела стало интервью американки кэтрин майорги немецкой газете der spiegel , в котором она рассказала о ситуации . майорги отметила , что получила 375 тысяч долларов за молчание от криштиану роналду , но в связи с движением она решила сделать все подробности публичными . издание daily mail , в свою очередь , сообщает , что португалец уже нанял детектива следить за девушкой . таким образом , роналду хочет дискредитировать 34-летнею американку . адвокаты звездного нападающего , как и сам игрок , отрицают все обвинения .

column1: 205677;instagram;2019-02-08 22:44:15;FALSE;"tarana burke has worked tirlessly to raise awareness of sexual violence and assault in our society. she began the #metoo movement in 2006 and gained national recognition in 2017 after victims of sexual harassment began to share their stories. ⁣

column1: 205795;instagram;2019-02-09 01:10:03;FALSE;"something terrible happened to me 4 years ago and you'd think i'd be over it by now but sometimes i'm not!
but i have to remind myself that things are better
column2: now. i have better friends and a better lifestyle. most importantly
column3: i found the love that i was looking for back then.

column1: it gets better. and it has.

column1: 205834;instagram;2019-02-09 02:09:35;FALSE;"this is the first post in a series about inspiring women from the last year. #womenof2018 #getsumart

every woman had their heart caught in their throat while listening to dr. ford give her testimony during the supreme court confirmation hearings for brett kavanaugh. too many women were able to point to a similar occasions in their pasts
column2: proving that incidents like these (no matter how big or small) affect women in unexpected ways for the rest of their lives.

column1: even though her testimony didn’t affect the outcome of the confirmation hearing

column1: 205881;instagram;2019-02-09 03:57:33;FALSE;"when we expose our souls to a broken and hurting world we are susceptible to their pessimism.

everyone has an opinion but what do you do when their verbal vomit is being aimed at you or your family? fight or flight? eye for an eye? it’s hard to love like jesus when you feel personally attacked.

column2: to say the least and considering how much i share it’s a miracle i haven’t received more negativity than i have. it honestly is few and far between. thus far i’ve been blessed with an amazing group of humans who truly love to encourage and lift others up. it’s beautiful.

column1: after receiving a few harsh judgments and unkind words yesterday i again questioned if i’m doing the right thing. should i open myself and my family up to this often cruel world? simply put ... yes.
for every rude or disrespectful comment i’ve received
column2: i’ve received 100 more explaining how my vulnerability has blessed them. i’ve made connections and exposed a new perspective for many. i’ve been lifted up and encouraged. so
column3: despite the cynicism i will continue to write. i will share and show love because if we retaliate with “an eye for an eye” the whole world would be blind and if we allowed the critics to silence us who would be left to inspire the world?

column1: you are the reason i am able to swallow my pride and expose my hard truths. i am brave and bold because the spirit lives within me but a loving and supportive tribe sure makes it a little easier so thank you for loving me.";;en;;;;;;0;;mccloudlife;Raquel McCloud;;0;False;30;0;0;114;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/67d9da89cd4674b62c52534752094ee0/5D14FBE6/t51.2885-15/e35/50603792_442117069659829_1598820067597504050_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"when we expose our souls to a broken and hurting world we are susceptible to their pessimism.

column1: 205899;instagram;2019-02-09 05:17:44;FALSE;"our theme #anodetowomen represents layers of steps of rising from individual consciousness to a collective one. our inspiration is a story of a girl & a predator that started from our first festival. but that story no longer belongs to that predator. that story has become about that one girl and her journey to healing.
it starts from a past rooted in pain: a kind of pain that gives one depth
column2: and moves towards healing: here there are breaths to be taken & a lesson to be recalled. lesson that height is just as important as depth to create balance & height cannot be reached without tending to the wounds that the depth brought with it. finally
column3: liberation: giving your emotions the worth they deserve
column4: growing out of the societal expectations
column5: choosing to not let yourself be defined by anyone or anything else other than yourself
column6: & eventually rising above own self image as well to open your inner eyes to see how limitless you are. we chose a woman to reflect this journey of rising above because we believe it starts with her. she represents & educates the family
column8: and will eventually walk the world towards healing with her sensitivity as her strength & vulnerability as her armor. because she makes the family
column9: the community. nothing can be talked about without including her in it

column1: when we talk about deep rooted issues in the society
column2: we must zoom our lenses in to the precious sensitivity of our children. starting with our girl child. is there something wrong with the way we raise her so that she grows but grows confined within the shape we want her to grow in? could it be the reason for her inability to comprehend the worth of her choice and opinions in her later life? are we building a prison for her with our own hands when we forbid her to feel an emotion? let's take anger: anger is a powerful emotion; it warns us of threat
column4: indignity and harm. but across the world
column5: girls and women are taught that their anger is better left unvoiced. why is that
column6: and what might we lose in this silence? isn't it a dangerous lie that anger isn't feminine? #lahootimelo2019 #lm2019 #lahooti #lahootimelo";;en;#AnOdeToWomen

column1: 205939;instagram;2019-02-09 06:55:20;FALSE;"after going to my favorite meeting in beverly hills i stopped by @crustaceanbh to celebrate!! sadly they have no non alcoholic beer on the menu and the liquor laws prevent me from being allowed to drink the non alcoholic ipa i found earlier today 😥

column2: said non alcoholic beer does not sell and certainly weren't kind about it. i understand that it's not the most popular item so i brought my own and was still treated poorly and decided that i wasn't interested in spending my money there. the door man was incredibly kind about it and tried to cheer me up but it's amazing to me how we expect anyone to stay sober when we don't offer any non alcoholic beer and then are rude to them for asking and being upset! they said just drink water. i don't want to drink water!!!!!

column1: i ended up eating grocery store food alone 😥 i was so hungry and my friend had an early flight. tomorrow i can try again i guess lol

#年假追劇最佳選擇 影集《性愛自修室》，因探討青少年的性啟蒙議題，並大膽拍攝性愛場景，引發不少關注。雖然影史上呈現性愛場景並非新鮮事，但因過程牽涉演員隱私、感受，令其拍攝不僅有一定難度，許多劇組還因此與演員發生爭執，進而導致法律糾紛。
本文將介紹拍攝性愛場景時，劇組務必進行的前置作業和現場調度，並分享拍攝《性愛成癮的男人》、《格雷的五十道陰影》等片時的實用技巧，讓劇組和演員都能在明確指示下，於安全工作環境裡進行拍攝。

잘먹눈데 못먹는 척하고 갖고싶은거 필요없눈 척하고 하고싶은거 아껴놓고 그림도 못구리는데 벽화한답시고 정리도 잘안하면서 결벽증인척하고 소심한데 대범한 척하고 할줄아는것도 없는데 다 하려러고 무능함이 재능인줄 알면서 남도와주면 행복 할 줄만 알었눈데 재미없고 집 놓어두고 타지에서 개고생 돈주고 하고 돈도 없는데 자꾸 집에서 안살라고 밖에 나가고 꽃은 드럽게 좋아하는데 주변사람들한테 주고 싶어하진 않고... 죽고 싶어고 아무것도 안할려 했는데 오지렆이 드럽게 태평양 만큼 넓어서 쓸떼기 없에 까인다.
라디오 mc전현무 형님을 너므좋아해서...무디를 디게 좋아해서... 뭐든 무디다.
군살이 생기면 단단해 보일 줄 알았눈데 드러워 보인단걸 몰랐다.
삶의 무게도 모르고 좋은 것만 찾는 요즘 것들과 비교하면 정말 바보지만... 그냥 그렇게 사는게 재미지다.
조금 더 살면 행복이 뭔지 조금 알 수도 있겠지...
두개의보드가 벨런스와 휠의 회전이 일장하면 좋겠지만
